  "output": "## Test Coverage Analysis — jobsquare\n\n**Current state: zero tests exist anywhere in the repo** (`find . -iname \"*test*\" -name \"*.py\"` only hits `.venv` internals). No `pytest`, `respx`, or `freezegun` installed either. Everything below assumes you add:\n\n```\n# requirements-dev.txt\npytest>=8.0\npytest-asyncio>=0.24\nrespx>=0.21          # mock httpx at the transport layer\nfreezegun>=1.5        # freeze datetime.now() for posted_at/cutoff tests\n```\n\nCoverage is 0% across all 8 modules (1,932 lines). I've ranked gaps by risk. `fetchers.py` (1,146 lines, 20+ ATS integrations) is by far the largest and riskiest surface — its `parse_*` functions are pure and cheap to test; its `fetch_*` functions need `respx` mocking for pagination/retry logic.\n\n---\n\n### 1. `models.py` — untested: `parse_posted_at`, `Job.key`, `Job.content_hash`, `Job.to_row`\n\n**Gaps:**\n- Epoch boundary: is 999999999999 (12 digits, just under 1e12) treated as seconds while 1000000000000 is ms? Off-by-one in the digit-count heuristic is untested.\n- Negative epoch (`\"-1\"` matches `lstrip(\"-\").isdigit()`).\n- ISO string without `Z`/offset → should get UTC attached.\n- Malformed string → `None`, not an exception.\n- `content_hash` must NOT change when `posted_at`/`salary_range` change (it's excluded from the hash blob), but MUST change when title/location/url/department change — this asymmetry is exactly the kind of thing a silent regression breaks.\n- `to_row()` must drop `raw` and add computed `key`/`content_hash`.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_models.py\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import timezone\nfrom models import Job, parse_posted_at\n\nclass TestParsePostedAt:\n    def test_empty_returns_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"\") is None\n\n    @pytest.mark.parametrize(\"value,expected_epoch\", [\n        (\"1643241332430\", 1643241332),   # lever ms epoch\n        (\"1643241332\", 1643241332),      # plain seconds epoch\n        (\"-1\", -1),                      # negative epoch edge case\n    ])\n    def test_epoch_variants(self, value, expected_epoch):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(value)\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n        assert int(dt.timestamp()) == expected_epoch\n\n    def test_iso_without_offset_assumes_utc(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2026-01-15T10:00:00\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_iso_z_suffix(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2026-01-15T10:00:00Z\")\n        assert dt is not None and dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_unparseable_prose_returns_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"Posted 3 Days Ago\") is None  # Workday format\n\n    def test_whitespace_only_returns_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"   \") is None\n\n\nclass TestJobIdentity:\n    def _job(self, **overrides):\n        base = dict(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                     title=\"Engineer\", url=\"https://x\", location=\"NYC\",\n                     department=\"Eng\")\n        return Job(**{**base, **overrides})\n\n    def test_key_format(self):\n        assert self._job().key == \"greenhouse:acme:1\"\n\n    def test_content_hash_stable_across_posted_at_and_salary(self):\n        a = self._job(posted_at=\"2026-01-01\", salary_range=\"100k\")\n        b = self._job(posted_at=\"2026-06-01\", salary_range=\"200k\")\n        assert a.content_hash == b.content_hash\n\n    @pytest.mark.parametrize(\"field,value\", [\n        (\"title\", \"Senior Engineer\"), (\"location\", \"SF\"),\n        (\"url\", \"https://y\"), (\"department\", \"Sales\"),\n    ])\n    def test_content_hash_changes_on_material_fields(self, field, value):\n        a = self._job()\n        b = self._job(**{field: value})\n        assert a.content_hash != b.content_hash\n\n    def test_to_row_excludes_raw_includes_computed_fields(self):\n        j = self._job(raw={\"secret\": \"data\"})\n        row = j.to_row()\n        assert \"raw\" not in row\n        assert row[\"key\"] == j.key\n        assert row[\"content_hash\"] == j.content_hash\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `filters.py` — untested: `match`, `filter_jobs`\n\n**Gaps:**\n- Word-boundary regex (`\\b`) means `\"AI\"` shouldn't false-match inside `\"Maintain\"` — this is a real correctness property worth pinning.\n- `exclude` short-circuits before `include` is even checked.\n- Unparseable `posted_dt` must survive the cutoff filter (explicit \"keep, don't nuke\" comment in code — easy to regress).\n- Location matching is substring + case-insensitive.\n- `max_age_days` accepts a float string like `\"3.5\"`.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_filters.py\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nfrom models import Job\nfrom filters import match, filter_jobs\n\ndef _job(title=\"Software Engineer\", dept=\"\", loc=\"Remote\", posted_at=\"\"):\n    return Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=title,\n               url=\"u\", department=dept, location=loc, posted_at=posted_at)\n\nclass TestMatch:\n    def test_word_boundary_avoids_substring_false_positive(self):\n        # \"AI\" should not match inside \"Maintain\"\n        assert match(_job(title=\"Maintain the pipeline\"), include=[\"AI\"]) is False\n\n    def test_include_keyword_matches_whole_word_case_insensitive(self):\n        assert match(_job(title=\"Machine Learning AI Engineer\"), include=[\"ai\"]) is True\n\n    def test_exclude_takes_priority_over_include(self):\n        j = _job(title=\"Staff Engineer\", dept=\"Sales\")\n        assert match(j, include=[\"Engineer\"], exclude=[\"Sales\"]) is False\n\n    def test_location_substring_case_insensitive(self):\n        assert match(_job(loc=\"San Francisco, CA\"), locations=[\"san francisco\"]) is True\n\n    def test_location_no_match(self):\n        assert match(_job(loc=\"London\"), locations=[\"New York\"]) is False\n\n    def test_cutoff_drops_confirmed_old_posting(self):\n        old = _job(posted_at=(datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=30)).isoformat())\n        cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=7)\n        assert match(old, cutoff=cutoff) is False\n\n    def test_cutoff_keeps_unparseable_date_instead_of_dropping(self):\n        j = _job(posted_at=\"Posted 3 Days Ago\")  # Workday prose, unparseable\n        cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=1)\n        assert match(j, cutoff=cutoff) is True\n\n    def test_no_rules_matches_everything(self):\n        assert match(_job()) is True\n\n\nclass TestFilterJobs:\n    def test_max_age_days_accepts_float_string(self):\n        fresh = _job(posted_at=datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat())\n        stale = _job(posted_at=(datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=10)).isoformat())\n        out = filter_jobs([fresh, stale], {\"max_age_days\": \"3.5\"})\n        assert out == [fresh]\n\n    def test_empty_rules_returns_all_jobs(self):\n        jobs = [_job(), _job(external_id=\"2\")]\n        assert filter_jobs(jobs, {}) == jobs\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. `store.py` — untested: `Store.diff`, `_migrate`, `next_seq`, `added_since`, `count`\n\n**Gaps:**\n- The three-way branch in `diff`: brand-new key vs changed `content_hash` vs unchanged (only `last_seen` bumped) — none tested.\n- `_migrate` adding `salary_range` to a pre-existing DB missing that column — this is exactly the kind of thing that silently breaks on upgrade and nobody notices until prod.\n- `added_since` boundary: strictly `>`, not `>=` — an off-by-one here would replay or drop rows on every scan.\n- `next_seq` concurrency claim (docstring says `BEGIN IMMEDIATE` prevents races) is completely unverified.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_store.py\nimport sqlite3\nimport pytest\nfrom models import Job\nfrom store import Store\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef store(tmp_path):\n    s = Store(tmp_path / \"test.db\")\n    yield s\n    s.close()\n\ndef _job(ext_id=\"1\", title=\"Engineer\"):\n    return Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=ext_id,\n               title=title, url=\"https://x\", location=\"NYC\")\n\nclass TestDiff:\n    def test_first_seen_job_is_new(self, store):\n        new, changed = store.diff([_job()])\n        assert len(new) == 1 and changed == []\n\n    def test_unchanged_job_reported_neither_new_nor_changed(self, store):\n        store.diff([_job()])\n        new, changed = store.diff([_job()])\n        assert new == [] and changed == []\n\n    def test_content_change_reported_as_changed(self, store):\n        store.diff([_job(title=\"Engineer I\")])\n        new, changed = store.diff([_job(title=\"Engineer II\")])\n        assert new == [] and len(changed) == 1\n\n    def test_unchanged_job_still_bumps_last_seen(self, store):\n        store.diff([_job()])\n        store.diff([_job()])\n        row = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT last_seen, first_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()\n        assert row[\"last_seen\"] >= row[\"first_seen\"]\n\n\nclass TestMigration:\n    def test_migrate_adds_salary_range_to_legacy_db(self, tmp_path):\n        path = tmp_path / \"legacy.db\"\n        conn = sqlite3.connect(path)\n        conn.execute(\"\"\"CREATE TABLE jobs (key TEXT PRIMARY KEY, source TEXT,\n            company TEXT, external_id TEXT, title TEXT, url TEXT, location TEXT,\n            department TEXT, employment_type TEXT, posted_at TEXT,\n            content_hash TEXT, first_seen TEXT, last_seen TEXT)\"\"\")  # no salary_range\n        conn.commit(); conn.close()\n\n        s = Store(path)  # should not raise\n        cols = {r[\"name\"] for r in s.conn.execute(\"PRAGMA table_info(jobs)\")}\n        assert \"salary_range\" in cols\n        s.close()\n\n\nclass TestAddedSince:\n    def test_strictly_after_excludes_boundary_timestamp(self, store):\n        store.diff([_job()])\n        ts = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT first_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()[0]\n        assert store.added_since(ts) == []  # not >=\n\n    def test_ordering_oldest_first(self, store):\n        store.diff([_job(ext_id=\"1\")])\n        store.diff([_job(ext_id=\"2\")])\n        rows = store.added_since(\"2000-01-01T00:00:00\")\n        assert [r[\"external_id\"] for r in rows] == [\"1\", \"2\"]\n\n\nclass TestNextSeq:\n    def test_increments_from_one(self, store):\n        assert store.next_seq(\"report_seq\") == 1\n        assert store.next_seq(\"report_seq\") == 2\n\n    def test_independent_keys_do_not_share_counter(self, store):\n        store.next_seq(\"a\")\n        assert store.next_seq(\"b\") == 1\n\n\ndef test_count_reflects_row_count(store):\n    assert store.count() == 0\n    store.diff([_job()])\n    assert store.count() == 1\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. `notify.py` — untested: every notifier + `dispatch`'s error isolation\n\n**Gaps:**\n- Every notifier's \"no env var → no-op\" and \"env var set but no jobs → no-op\" branches (`not (new or changed)`).\n- **`dispatch`'s core contract is untested**: one notifier raising must not stop the others. This is the most important test in the file — right now nothing proves it works.\n- `_sms_body` truncation at `limit=8` and the `+N more` line.\n- Slack/webhook/SMS payload shape (needs `respx` or `monkeypatch` on `httpx.post`).\n\n```python\n# tests/test_notify.py\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import patch, MagicMock\nfrom models import Job\nimport notify\n\ndef _job(title=\"Eng\", company=\"acme\"):\n    return Job(source=\"s\", company=company, external_id=\"1\", title=title, url=\"u\")\n\nclass TestDispatchErrorIsolation:\n    def test_one_notifier_failing_does_not_block_others(self, capsys):\n        calls = []\n        def ok(new, changed): calls.append(\"ok\")\n        def boom(new, changed): raise RuntimeError(\"smtp down\")\n        with patch.object(notify, \"NOTIFIERS\", [boom, ok]):\n            notify.dispatch([_job()], [])\n        assert calls == [\"ok\"]\n        assert \"boom\" in capsys.readouterr().out or \"failed\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n\n\nclass TestSlackNotifier:\n    def test_noop_when_env_var_unset(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.delenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", raising=False)\n        with patch(\"notify.httpx.post\") as post:\n            notify.notify_slack([_job()], [])\n            post.assert_not_called()\n\n    def test_noop_when_no_jobs_even_with_url_set(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"https://hooks.slack.com/x\")\n        with patch(\"notify.httpx.post\") as post:\n            notify.notify_slack([], [])\n            post.assert_not_called()\n\n    def test_posts_payload_with_job_details(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"https://hooks.slack.com/x\")\n        with patch(\"notify.httpx.post\") as post:\n            notify.notify_slack([_job(title=\"Staff Eng\")], [])\n            _, kwargs = post.call_args\n            assert \"Staff Eng\" in kwargs[\"json\"][\"text\"]\n\n\nclass TestSmsBody:\n    def test_truncates_at_limit_and_shows_remainder_count(self):\n        jobs = [_job(title=f\"Role {i}\") for i in range(10)]\n        body = notify._sms_body(jobs, [], limit=8)\n        assert body.count(\"Role\") == 8\n        assert \"+2 more\" in body\n\n    def test_ascii_only_no_smart_punctuation(self):\n        body = notify._sms_body([_job()], [])\n        assert \"•\" not in body and \"…\" not in body\n\n\nclass TestSmsNotifier:\n    @pytest.mark.parametrize(\"missing_var\", [\n        \"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\", \"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\", \"TWILIO_FROM\", \"TWILIO_TO\"])\n    def test_noop_if_any_required_env_var_missing(self, monkeypatch, missing_var):\n        env = {\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\": \"sid\", \"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\": \"tok\",\n               \"TWILIO_FROM\": \"+1\", \"TWILIO_TO\": \"+2\"}\n        env.pop(missing_var)\n        for k, v in env.items():\n            monkeypatch.setenv(k, v)\n        monkeypatch.delenv(missing_var, raising=False)\n        with patch(\"notify.httpx.post\") as post:\n            notify.notify_sms([_job()], [])\n            post.assert_not_called()\n\n    def test_raises_on_twilio_error_response(self, monkeypatch):\n        for k, v in {\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\": \"sid\", \"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\": \"tok\",\n                     \"TWILIO_FROM\": \"+1\", \"TWILIO_TO\": \"+2\"}.items():\n            monkeypatch.setenv(k, v)\n        resp = MagicMock()\n        resp.raise_for_status.side_effect = Exception(\"401 unauthorized\")\n        with patch(\"notify.httpx.post\", return_value=resp):\n            with pytest.raises(Exception):\n                notify.notify_sms([_job()], [])\n\n\nclass TestEmailNotifier:\n    def test_noop_when_smtp_host_unset(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.delenv(\"SMTP_HOST\", raising=False)\n        with patch(\"notify.smtplib.SMTP\") as smtp:\n            notify.notify_email([_job()], [])\n            smtp.assert_not_called()\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. `pipeline.py` — untested: `load_config` defaults, `run` (dry-run vs real), integration wiring\n\n**Gaps:**\n- `load_config` default-filling when `sources`/`filters`/`db`/`concurrency` are absent from the YAML.\n- `dry_run=True` must never touch the `Store` (no dedup state written) and must return `new=0, changed=0`.\n- Real run must call `fetch_all → filter_jobs → store.diff → dispatch` in that order with correct data flowing through — this is your one true integration test and it doesn't exist.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_pipeline.py\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import patch, AsyncMock\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom models import Job\nimport pipeline\n\nclass TestLoadConfig:\n    def test_fills_defaults_for_missing_keys(self, tmp_path):\n        cfg_path = tmp_path / \"min.yaml\"\n        cfg_path.write_text(\"sources: []\\n\")\n        cfg = pipeline.load_config(cfg_path)\n        assert cfg[\"db\"] == \"jobs.db\"\n        assert cfg[\"concurrency\"] == 8\n        assert cfg[\"filters\"] == {}\n\n\nclass TestRun:\n    @pytest.fixture\n    def cfg_path(self, tmp_path):\n        p = tmp_path / \"cfg.yaml\"\n        p.write_text(f\"sources: [{{ats: greenhouse, company: acme}}]\\ndb: {tmp_path/'t.db'}\\n\")\n        return p\n\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_dry_run_does_not_persist_to_store(self, cfg_path, tmp_path):\n        job = Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                   title=\"Eng\", url=\"u\")\n        with patch(\"pipeline.fetch_all\", new=AsyncMock(return_value=[job])):\n            result = await pipeline.run(cfg_path, dry_run=True)\n        assert result == {\"matched\": 1, \"new\": 0, \"changed\": 0}\n        assert not Path(tmp_path / \"t.db\").exists()\n\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_real_run_persists_and_dispatches(self, cfg_path):\n        job = Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                   title=\"Eng\", url=\"u\")\n        with patch(\"pipeline.fetch_all\", new=AsyncMock(return_value=[job])), \\\n             patch(\"pipeline.dispatch\") as dispatch:\n            result = await pipeline.run(cfg_path, dry_run=False)\n        assert result[\"new\"] == 1\n        dispatch.assert_called_once()\n        new_arg, changed_arg = dispatch.call_args[0]\n        assert new_arg == [job]\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. `fetchers.py` — the biggest gap by far\n\n#### 6a. The retry/HTTP core (`_request`) — **found a real bug via this analysis**\n\nReading `_request` closely: `r.raise_for_status()` raises `httpx.HTTPStatusError` for *any* 4xx/5xx, and that's caught by the same `except (httpx.TransportError, httpx.HTTPStatusError)` clause as the explicitly-retryable codes. That means a `404 Not Found` (a permanent, non-transient error) gets retried up to 4 times with exponential backoff before failing — wasted latency on every genuinely-missing resource. This should be tested and probably fixed (only retry the listed transient codes).\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers_request.py\nimport httpx\nimport pytest\nimport respx\nfrom fetchers import _request, _get_json\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nclass TestRequestRetry:\n    async def test_retries_on_503_then_succeeds(self, respx_mock):\n        route = respx_mock.get(\"https://x/jobs\").mock(\n            side_effect=[httpx.Response(503), httpx.Response(200, json={\"ok\": True})])\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            r = await _request(client, \"https://x/jobs\", retries=2)\n        assert r.status_code == 200\n        assert route.call_count == 2\n\n    async def test_exhausts_retries_and_raises_runtime_error(self, respx_mock):\n        respx_mock.get(\"https://x/jobs\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(500))\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"failed to fetch\"):\n                await _request(client, \"https://x/jobs\", retries=2)\n\n    async def test_404_is_retried_needlessly(self, respx_mock):\n        # documents current (arguably buggy) behavior: a permanent 404 still\n        # burns through all retry attempts before failing.\n        route = respx_mock.get(\"https://x/jobs\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(404))\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n                await _request(client, \"https://x/jobs\", retries=3)\n        assert route.call_count == 3  # currently retries a non-transient error\n\n    async def test_transport_error_is_retried(self, respx_mock):\n        respx_mock.get(\"https://x/jobs\").mock(side_effect=httpx.ConnectError(\"boom\"))\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n                await _request(client, \"https://x/jobs\", retries=2)\n```\n\n#### 6b. Pure `parse_*` normalizers — no network needed, high value, currently 0% covered\n\nThere are 15+ of these. Pattern (repeat per source, adjusting fixture payload):\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers_parsers.py\nfrom fetchers import (parse_greenhouse, parse_lever, _lever_salary, parse_ashby,\n                       parse_ashby_page, parse_smartrecruiters, parse_recruitee,\n                       parse_workable, parse_google, _extract_ds1, _ds1_posted_at,\n                       parse_deshaw, parse_twosigma, parse_optiver, parse_apple,\n                       _apple_posted_at, parse_eightfold, parse_bytedance,\n                       _bd_location, parse_phenom, parse_amazon, _amazon_posted_at)\n\nclass TestParseGreenhouse:\n    def test_maps_fields_and_joins_departments(self):\n        data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"Eng\", \"absolute_url\": \"u\",\n                           \"location\": {\"name\": \"NYC\"},\n                           \"departments\": [{\"name\": \"Eng\"}, {\"name\": \"Platform\"}],\n                           \"updated_at\": \"2026-01-01\"}]}\n        out = parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", data)\n        assert len(out) == 1\n        assert out[0].department == \"Eng, Platform\"\n\n    def test_missing_location_defaults_empty(self):\n        out = parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"Eng\"}]})\n        assert out[0].location == \"\"\n\n    def test_no_jobs_key_returns_empty_list(self):\n        assert parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", {}) == []\n\n\nclass TestLeverSalary:\n    def test_formats_min_max_with_currency_and_commas(self):\n        j = {\"salaryRange\": {\"min\": 100000, \"max\": 150000, \"currency\": \"USD\"}}\n        assert _lever_salary(j) == \"USD 100,000–150,000\"\n\n    def test_falls_back_to_description_when_no_range(self):\n        j = {\"salaryDescriptionPlain\": \"Competitive\"}\n        assert _lever_salary(j) == \"Competitive\"\n\n    def test_no_salary_data_returns_empty_string(self):\n        assert _lever_salary({}) == \"\"\n\n\nclass TestParseAshby:\n    def test_skips_unlisted_jobs(self):\n        data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": \"1\", \"isListed\": False, \"title\": \"Hidden\"},\n                          {\"id\": \"2\", \"isListed\": True, \"title\": \"Visible\"}]}\n        out = parse_ashby(\"co\", data)\n        assert len(out) == 1 and out[0].title == \"Visible\"\n\n    def test_external_id_falls_back_to_jobId(self):\n        out = parse_ashby(\"co\", {\"jobs\": [{\"jobId\": \"j1\", \"title\": \"T\"}]})\n        assert out[0].external_id == \"j1\"\n\n\nclass TestExtractDs1AndPostedAt:\n    def test_extracts_valid_blob(self):\n        html = \"key: 'ds:1', ... data:[[[1,\\\"Job\\\"]]] , sideChannel:{}\"\n        assert _extract_ds1(html) == [[1, \"Job\"]]\n\n    def test_missing_key_returns_empty_list(self):\n        assert _extract_ds1(\"<html>no data here</html>\") == []\n\n    def test_malformed_json_returns_empty_list(self):\n        html = \"key: 'ds:1', data:[not valid json] , sideChannel:{}\"\n        assert _extract_ds1(html) == []\n\n    def test_ds1_posted_at_prefers_create_over_update_time(self):\n        job = [None] * 15\n        job[12] = [1700000000, 0]   # create\n        job[13] = [1800000000, 0]   # update\n        assert \"2023\" in _ds1_posted_at(job) or _ds1_posted_at(job) != \"\"\n\n    def test_ds1_posted_at_falls_back_when_create_missing(self):\n        job = [None] * 15\n        job[13] = [1700000000, 0]\n        assert _ds1_posted_at(job) != \"\"\n\n    def test_ds1_posted_at_no_timestamps_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _ds1_posted_at([None] * 15) == \"\"\n\n\nclass TestParseDeshaw:\n    def test_dedups_by_job_id(self):\n        page = ('<div data-job-id=\"1\"><span class=\"job-display-name\">A</span>'\n                 '</div><div data-job-id=\"1\"><span class=\"job-display-name\">A</span></div>')\n        out = parse_deshaw(\"deshaw\", page)\n        assert len(out) == 1\n\n    def test_unescapes_html_entities_in_title(self):\n        page = '<div data-job-id=\"1\"><span class=\"job-display-name\">R&amp;D Eng</span></div>'\n        out = parse_deshaw(\"deshaw\", page)\n        assert out[0].title == \"R&D Eng\"\n\n\nclass TestParseTwosigma:\n    def test_dedups_role_rendered_three_times(self):\n        page = ('href=\"https://careers.twosigma.com/careers/JobDetail/x/1\">Eng</a>' * 3)\n        out = parse_twosigma(\"twosigma\", page)\n        assert len(out) == 1\n\n\nclass TestParseOptiver:\n    def test_strips_join_us_jobs_prefix_for_external_id(self):\n        j = {\"href\": \"/join-us/jobs/eng/nyc/software-engineer\", \"title\": \"SWE\"}\n        out = parse_optiver(\"optiver\", [j])\n        assert out[0].external_id == \"eng/nyc/software-engineer\"\n\n\nclass TestApplePostedAt:\n    def test_trims_nanosecond_precision_to_microseconds(self):\n        assert _apple_posted_at(\"2026-01-15T10:00:03.812668311Z\") == \\\n            \"2026-01-15T10:00:03.812668+00:00\"\n\n    def test_empty_value_returns_empty_string(self):\n        assert _apple_posted_at(\"\") == \"\"\n\n\nclass TestBdLocation:\n    def test_walks_parent_chain_city_state_country(self):\n        city = {\"en_name\": \"Seattle\",\n                \"parent\": {\"en_name\": \"WA\", \"parent\": {\"en_name\": \"USA\", \"parent\": None}}}\n        assert _bd_location(city) == \"Seattle, WA, USA\"\n\n    def test_none_returns_empty_string(self):\n        assert _bd_location(None) == \"\"\n\n\nclass TestAmazonPostedAt:\n    def test_parses_us_format_date(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"June 26, 2026\") == \"2026-06-26T00:00:00+00:00\"\n\n    def test_malformed_date_returns_empty_string(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"not a date\") == \"\"\n\n    def test_unknown_month_returns_empty_string(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"Frobtember 1, 2026\") == \"\"\n\n\nclass TestParsePhenom:\n    def test_job_seq_no_fallback_when_job_id_missing(self):\n        out = parse_phenom(\"co\", [{\"jobSeqNo\": \"seq-1\", \"title\": \"T\"}])\n        assert out[0].external_id == \"seq-1\"\n```\n\n#### 6c. Pagination-loop `fetch_*` functions — need `respx`, currently untested\n\nThese all share the same shape (loop until a page returns nothing new, dedup by `external_id`, respect `max_pages`). Test the shared contract once thoroughly on one representative (e.g. `fetch_optiver`), then pin the source-specific quirks:\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers_pagination.py\nimport httpx, pytest\nfrom fetchers import fetch_optiver, fetch_workday, fetch_ashby\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nclass TestPaginationContract:\n    async def test_stops_when_page_returns_no_new_items(self, respx_mock):\n        respx_mock.get(\"https://www.optiver.com/en/api/v1/jobs\").mock(\n            side_effect=[\n                httpx.Response(200, json={\"items\": [{\"href\": \"/a\", \"title\": \"A\"}]}),\n                httpx.Response(200, json={\"items\": []}),\n            ])\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            jobs = await fetch_optiver(client, {\"company\": \"optiver\"})\n        assert len(jobs) == 1\n\n    async def test_respects_max_pages_cap(self, respx_mock):\n        respx_mock.get(\"https://www.optiver.com/en/api/v1/jobs\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(200, json={\"items\": [{\"href\": \"/x\", \"title\": \"X\"}]}))\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            jobs = await fetch_optiver(client, {\"company\": \"optiver\", \"max_pages\": 2})\n        assert len(jobs) <= 2  # bounded despite endless \"new\" items\n\n\nclass TestFetchWorkday:\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_safety_cap_at_5000_offset_stops_loop(self, respx_mock):\n        # server never signals \"done\" (total keeps exceeding offset) — must\n        # still terminate via the `offset > 5000` safety cap, not hang forever.\n        respx_mock.post(url__regex=r\".*/wday/cxs/.*\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(200, json={\n                \"jobPostings\": [{\"title\": \"T\", \"externalPath\": \"/job/1\"}],\n                \"total\": 999999}))\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            jobs = await fetch_workday(client, {\"host\": \"h\", \"tenant\": \"t\", \"site\": \"s\"})\n        assert len(jobs) > 0  # terminated, didn't hang\n\n\nclass TestFetchAshby:\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_uses_posting_api_when_available(self, respx_mock):\n        respx_mock.get(url__regex=r\"api\\.ashbyhq\\.com.*\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobs\": [{\"id\": \"1\", \"title\": \"T\"}]}))\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            jobs = await fetch_ashby(client, {\"company\": \"acme\"})\n        assert len(jobs) == 1\n\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_falls_back_to_hosted_page_on_404(self, respx_mock):\n        respx_mock.get(url__regex=r\"api\\.ashbyhq\\.com.*\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(404))\n        respx_mock.get(url__regex=r\"jobs\\.ashbyhq\\.com.*\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(200, text=(\n                'window.__appData = {\"jobBoard\":{\"jobPostings\":'\n                '[{\"id\":\"1\",\"title\":\"T\",\"isListed\":true}]}}')))\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            jobs = await fetch_ashby(client, {\"company\": \"acme\"})\n        assert len(jobs) == 1\n\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_raises_when_neither_posting_api_nor_appdata_present(self, respx_mock):\n        respx_mock.get(url__regex=r\"api\\.ashbyhq\\.com.*\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(404))\n        respx_mock.get(url__regex=r\"jobs\\.ashbyhq\\.com.*\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(200, text=\"<html>nothing</html>\"))\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"no posting-api\"):\n                await fetch_ashby(client, {\"company\": \"acme\"})\n```\n\n#### 6d. Fetch registry + fan-out (`fetch_source`, `fetch_all`) — **currently the least tested but most important integration point**\n\n```python\nclass TestFetchSource:\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_unknown_ats_raises_value_error(self):\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"unknown ATS\"):\n                await fetch_source(client, {\"ats\": \"bogus_ats\"})\n\n\nclass TestFetchAll:\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_one_source_failing_does_not_kill_the_run(self, respx_mock, capsys):\n        respx_mock.get(url__regex=r\"boards-api\\.greenhouse\\.io.*\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"T\"}]}))\n        respx_mock.get(url__regex=r\"api\\.lever\\.co.*\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(500))\n        sources = [{\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"good\"},\n                   {\"ats\": \"lever\", \"company\": \"bad\"}]\n        jobs = await fetch_all(sources, concurrency=2)\n        assert len(jobs) == 1  # good source's results survive the bad one's failure\n        assert \"failed\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_concurrency_limit_is_respected(self, respx_mock):\n        # 20 sources, concurrency=2 — assert peak concurrent in-flight <= 2\n        # (requires an instrumented mock transport tracking concurrent calls)\n        ...\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. `agent.py` — untested: `cmd_db_new`, `cmd_db_mark`, `_normalize_ats`, `cmd_pdf_render`, `_chrome_bin`\n\n**Gaps:**\n- `cmd_db_new`'s truncation logic only cuts at `first_seen` **group boundaries**, never splitting a group — the trickiest logic in the file, and completely unverified.\n- `--posted-days` + `--dated-only` interaction: undated jobs kept by default, dropped only with `--dated-only`.\n- `cmd_db_mark` rejects a non-ISO watermark (exit code 2) but accepts `--now`.\n- `_normalize_ats` must not touch text inside `<script>`/`<style>` or inside tag attributes — only body text between tags.\n- `_chrome_bin` discovery order: `CHROME_PATH` env → `which` → hardcoded app paths → `sys.exit`.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_agent.py\nimport json\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\nfrom store import Store\nfrom models import Job\nimport agent\n\nclass TestCmdDbNew:\n    @pytest.fixture\n    def db_with_jobs(self, tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n        db_path = tmp_path / \"jobs.db\"\n        cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n        cfg_path.write_text(f\"db: {db_path}\\n\")\n        with Store(db_path) as s:\n            s.diff([Job(source=\"gh\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"A\", url=\"u\")])\n        return cfg_path\n\n    def test_first_run_uses_since_days_window(self, db_with_jobs, capsys):\n        agent.cmd_db_new([\"-c\", str(db_with_jobs), \"--since-days\", \"7\"])\n        out = json.loads(capsys.readouterr().out)\n        assert out[\"first_run\"] is True\n        assert out[\"count\"] == 1\n\n    def test_truncation_never_splits_a_first_seen_group(self, tmp_path, capsys):\n        db_path = tmp_path / \"jobs.db\"\n        cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n        cfg_path.write_text(f\"db: {db_path}\\n\")\n        with Store(db_path) as s:\n            # two jobs in the SAME diff() call share one first_seen timestamp\n            s.diff([Job(source=\"gh\", company=\"c\", external_id=str(i), title=\"A\", url=\"u\")\n                     for i in range(3)])\n        agent.cmd_db_new([\"-c\", str(cfg_path), \"--limit\", \"2\"])\n        out = json.loads(capsys.readouterr().out)\n        # limit=2 but the group of 3 shares one first_seen -> group is atomic:\n        # either all 3 included (if jobs list was empty) or all excluded\n        assert out[\"count\"] in (0, 3)\n\n    def test_dated_only_drops_undated_rows(self, db_with_jobs, capsys):\n        agent.cmd_db_new([\"-c\", str(db_with_jobs), \"--dated-only\"])\n        out = json.loads(capsys.readouterr().out)\n        assert out[\"undated_dropped\"] >= 1\n        assert out[\"count\"] == 0  # the fixture job has no posted_at\n\n\nclass TestCmdDbMark:\n    def test_now_flag_sets_current_timestamp(self, tmp_path, capsys):\n        cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n        cfg_path.write_text(f\"db: {tmp_path/'jobs.db'}\\n\")\n        rc = agent.cmd_db_mark([\"--now\", \"-c\", str(cfg_path)])\n        assert rc == 0\n\n    def test_invalid_watermark_returns_exit_code_2(self, tmp_path, capsys):\n        cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n        cfg_path.write_text(f\"db: {tmp_path/'jobs.db'}\\n\")\n        rc = agent.cmd_db_mark([\"not-a-timestamp\", \"-c\", str(cfg_path)])\n        assert rc == 2\n\n    def test_neither_watermark_nor_now_returns_exit_code_2(self, tmp_path):\n        cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n        cfg_path.write_text(f\"db: {tmp_path/'jobs.db'}\\n\")\n        assert agent.cmd_db_mark([\"-c\", str(cfg_path)]) == 2\n\n\nclass TestNormalizeAts:\n    def test_replaces_em_dash_in_body_text(self):\n        html, counts = agent._normalize_ats(\"<p>foo\\u2014bar</p>\")\n        assert \"foo-bar\" in html\n        assert counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1\n\n    def test_does_not_modify_content_inside_script_tag(self):\n        html, counts = agent._normalize_ats(\n            \"<script>var x = 'a\\u2014b';</script><p>c\\u2014d</p>\")\n        assert \"a\\u2014b\" in html  # untouched inside script\n        assert \"c-d\" in html       # touched in body\n        assert counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1\n\n    def test_does_not_modify_tag_attributes(self):\n        html, counts = agent._normalize_ats('<a title=\"x\\u2014y\">z\\u2014w</a>')\n        assert 'title=\"x\\u2014y\"' in html  # attribute untouched\n        assert \"z-w\" in html\n\n    def test_no_special_chars_returns_empty_counts(self):\n        html, counts = agent._normalize_ats(\"<p>plain text</p>\")\n        assert counts == {}\n\n\nclass TestChromeBin:\n    def test_prefers_chrome_path_env_var_when_valid(self, monkeypatch, tmp_path):\n        fake = tmp_path / \"chrome\"\n        fake.write_text(\"\")\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"CHROME_PATH\", str(fake))\n        assert agent._chrome_bin() == str(fake)\n\n    def test_exits_when_nothing_found(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.delenv(\"CHROME_PATH\", raising=False)\n        with patch(\"agent.shutil.which\", return_value=None), \\\n             patch(\"agent.Path.exists\", return_value=False):\n            with pytest.raises(SystemExit):\n                agent._chrome_bin()\n\n\nclass TestCmdPdfRender:\n    def test_missing_input_file_returns_exit_code_2(self, tmp_path, capsys):\n        rc = agent.cmd_pdf_render([str(tmp_path / \"nope.html\")])\n        assert rc == 2\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. `cli.py` — thin, but the arg-parsing contract is untested\n\n```python\n# tests/test_cli.py\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\nimport cli\n\ndef test_dry_run_flag_forwarded_to_run_sync():\n    with patch(\"cli.run_sync\") as run_sync:\n        with patch(\"sys.argv\", [\"cli.py\", \"--dry-run\"]):\n            cli.main()\n        run_sync.assert_called_once_with(\"sources.yaml\", dry_run=True)\n\ndef test_default_config_path():\n    with patch(\"cli.run_sync\") as run_sync:\n        with patch(\"sys.argv\", [\"cli.py\"]):\n            cli.main()\n        run_sync.assert_called_once_with(\"sources.yaml\", dry_run=False)\n```\n\n---\n\n### Missing error-handling tests (cross-cutting)\n\n| Location | Untested failure mode |\n|---|---|\n| `fetchers._request` | 404 gets retried like a transient error (see 6a — likely a real bug) |\n| `notify.dispatch` | one notifier's exception must not block the rest — **your most important untested contract** |\n| `notify.notify_sms` | `resp.raise_for_status()` on Twilio failure — should propagate but currently untested |\n| `fetchers.fetch_all` | one source's exception is swallowed + logged, not fatal to the run |\n| `store.Store._migrate` | legacy DB missing `salary_range` column |\n| `agent.cmd_db_mark` | malformed watermark string → clean exit 2, not a stack trace |\n| `agent.cmd_pdf_render` | Chrome produces non-PDF output (`data.startswith(b\"%PDF\")` false) → exit 1 with stderr tail |\n| `fetchers.fetch_meta` | GraphQL response with `data.errors` (rotated `doc_id`) → `RuntimeError` with the error message surfaced |\n| `fetchers.fetch_ashby` | posting-api 5xx (not 404) should `raise_for_status()`, not silently fall back |\n\n### Integration test gaps\n\n1. **End-to-end pipeline run** with a fake in-memory `Store` and stubbed `fetch_all`/`dispatch` — proves fetch → filter → dedup → notify wiring survives refactors (skeleton in §5).\n2. **`agent.py db-new` → `db-mark` round trip**: dump jobs, advance the marker with the returned `watermark`, confirm the next `db-new` call doesn't re-emit the same rows (this is the core incremental-scan contract described in the module docstring and it's unverified).\n3. **Concurrent pipeline workers**: your own memory notes (`jobsquare-parallel-worker-collisions`) flag shared scratchpad/report-filename collisions under parallel runs — `Store.next_seq`'s `BEGIN IMMEDIATE` claim of atomicity has no concurrency test proving it actually serializes (e.g. spawn N threads/processes calling `next_seq` on the same key, assert no duplicate values).\n4. **Real ATS payload fixtures**: none of the `parse_*` tests above use captured real-world JSON — recommend saving 1–2 anonymized sample responses per ATS under `tests/fixtures/` (Ashby `isListed`, Apple's nanosecond timestamps, and ByteDance's strict body schema are the highest-risk shapes to pin against upstream changes).\n",
