        "content": "\n**Gaps:**\n- Epoch boundary: is 999999999999 (12 digits, just under 1e12) treated as seconds while 1000000000000 is ms? Off-by-one in the digit-count heuristic is untested.\n- Negative epoch (`\"-1\"` matches `lstrip(\"-\").isdigit()`).\n- ISO string without `Z`/offset → should get UTC attached.\n- Malformed string → `None`, not an exception.\n- `content_hash` must NOT change when `posted_at`/`salary_range` change (it's excluded from the hash blob), but MUST change when title/location/url/department change — this asymmetry is exactly the kind of thing a silent regression breaks.\n- `to_row()` must drop `raw` and add computed `key`/`content_hash`.\n\n```python\n",
